CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 1, 1950, pg. 12 reads: "Two Of A Kind - Mary Dee, left of radio Station WHOD pictured pinning a corsage on Jane Ellen Ball, director of women's activities at radio Station WJAS after Miss Ball had addressed a special session of the Charm Clinic at the Kay Boys' Club last Wednesday night. One hundred fifty teenage girls and women attended the event. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mary Dee wearing light colored dress with gathered front and detached sleeves, pinning corsage on Jane Ellen Ball, in Kay Boys Club for the Charm Clinic
